</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[198,1429,346,372]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,266,492]" box="[198,1429,346,372]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,346,372]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Distribution.</emphasis>
Circumglobal, except for eastern Pacific, at depths from 
<quantity box="[1022,1190,346,372]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="1200.0" valueMax="1600.0" valueMin="800.0">800 to 1600 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cohen, D. M. &amp; Hensley, D. A. &amp; Kimmel, J. J." box="[1204,1417,346,372]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" pagination="125 - 132" refId="ref15485" refString="Cohen, D. M.; Hensley, D. A. &amp; Kimmel, J. J. (1991) The deepsea ophidiid fish genus Lamprogrammus, a senior synonym of Bassobythites, with notes on the synonymy and distribution of L. brunswigi. Japanese Journal of Ichthyology, 38 (2), 125 - 132." type="journal article" year="1991">
Cohen 
<emphasis box="[1289,1347,346,371]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,266,492]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,386,412]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
First record in Brazilian waters. Collected from a single station off 
<collectingRegion box="[1107,1178,386,412]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, from 
<quantity box="[1253,1436,386,412]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0305" metricValueMax="1.049" metricValueMin="1.012" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="1030.5" valueMax="1049.0" valueMin="1012.0">1012 to 1049 m</quantity>
depth. A rare species, of which just 
<specimenCount box="[584,730,426,452]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" type="generic">9 specimens</specimenCount>
(including the two herein presented) larger than 
<quantity box="[1317,1391,426,452]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" unit="cm" value="90.0">90 cm</quantity>
are known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
